Because after I kicked it,

1888
01:00:35,720 --> 01:00:37,480
the lock broke, right?

1889
01:00:37,480 --> 01:00:40,000
But his foot was blocking the door.

1890
01:00:42,120 --> 01:00:43,780
A locked-room murder.

1891
01:00:43,940 --> 01:00:45,740
(Locked-room murder)
Exactly.

1892
01:00:45,760 --> 01:00:45,960
Okay.

1893
01:00:45,960 --> 01:00:47,000
That means

1894
01:00:47,560 --> 01:00:49,000
the killer didn't leave through here.

1895
01:00:49,000 --> 01:00:50,360
If they did, they
couldn't open the door.

1896
01:00:50,360 --> 01:00:52,400
Right. So this door

1897
01:00:52,400 --> 01:00:54,040
must've been closed first.

1898
01:00:54,880 --> 01:00:57,120
(The door was locked from inside)
He lay down after it was closed.

1899
01:00:57,120 --> 01:00:58,600
As for how the killer got out,

1900
01:00:58,600 --> 01:00:59,360
I think

1901
01:00:59,360 --> 01:01:01,200
there had to be another exit.

1902
01:01:01,200 --> 01:01:02,880
But he just said this.

1903
01:01:02,880 --> 01:01:03,400
Look.

1904
01:01:04,120 --> 01:01:05,480
All furniture in the Meeting Hall

1905
01:01:05,480 --> 01:01:06,480
is fixed to the floor.

1906
01:01:06,480 --> 01:01:08,360
This window, meaning this window,

1907
01:01:08,360 --> 01:01:10,040
only opens outward from inside.

1908
01:01:10,040 --> 01:01:12,880
So that means
someone could leave through it.

1909
01:01:13,100 --> 01:01:14,440
(Known only exit)
But

1910
01:01:14,440 --> 01:01:16,280
there's nothing near the window

1911
01:01:16,280 --> 01:01:17,800
to step on for qinggong.

1912
01:01:17,800 --> 01:01:20,240
Or maybe this person knows martial arts.

1913
01:01:20,240 --> 01:01:21,880
They'd still need something to step on.

1914
01:01:21,880 --> 01:01:23,960
So these were what they used.

1915
01:01:23,960 --> 01:01:25,080
(Ning Waver's theory:)
I think...

1916
01:01:25,080 --> 01:01:26,240
(The killer used bamboo slips as steps)
maybe they stacked them like this.

1917
01:01:26,240 --> 01:01:27,160
(Then escaped through the window)
Exactly.

1918
01:01:27,160 --> 01:01:28,120
That's why they're scattered.

1919
01:01:28,480 --> 01:01:29,360
These can be stacked.

1920
01:01:29,360 --> 01:01:30,200
Look.

1921
01:01:30,200 --> 01:01:30,400
Right.

1922
01:01:30,400 --> 01:01:30,800
Like this.

1923
01:01:31,320 --> 01:01:33,400
For example, could they make a few rows?

1924
01:01:33,400 --> 01:01:34,560
Then they could stand on it.

1925
01:01:34,560 --> 01:01:35,160
Right.

1926
01:01:35,160 --> 01:01:35,760
They could stand on it.

1927
01:01:36,660 --> 01:01:37,900
(The real Ning Waver)

1928
01:01:38,320 --> 01:01:38,880
Right.

1929
01:01:38,880 --> 01:01:41,280
They used these bamboo slips to make

1930
01:01:41,280 --> 01:01:42,920
(Chewing)
a board, or something to step on.

1931
01:01:42,920 --> 01:01:44,920
So they might've climbed out from here.

1932
01:01:48,060 --> 01:01:50,220
(Theory: the killer may have escaped
through this window)

1933
01:01:50,960 --> 01:01:52,000
Kid!

1934
01:01:52,520 --> 01:01:53,280
What?

1935
01:01:53,280 --> 01:01:54,160
Kid!

1936
01:01:55,100 --> 01:01:56,380
(Oh, kid)

1937
01:01:56,400 --> 01:01:57,800
A sound came from inside just now.

1938
01:01:58,920 --> 01:02:00,840
So there's another space behind this.

1939
01:02:00,840 --> 01:02:01,640
There's a secret room.

1940
01:02:01,640 --> 01:02:02,920
Take the painting down.

1941
01:02:02,920 --> 01:02:03,560
Nothing.

1942
01:02:03,560 --> 01:02:04,440
Nothing behind it?

1943
01:02:06,500 --> 01:02:07,620
(Meeting Hall)

1944
01:02:07,640 --> 01:02:08,680
Kid!

1945
01:02:08,680 --> 01:02:09,720
(Where's the switch
to open the secret room?)

1946
01:02:09,720 --> 01:02:10,760
Kid!

1947
01:02:12,160 --> 01:02:12,960
Search the scene.

1948
01:02:18,380 --> 01:02:19,740
(Target spotted)

1949
01:02:23,000 --> 01:02:23,640
Anyone?

1950
01:02:23,640 --> 01:02:25,440
Anyone wants to twist it with me?

1951
01:02:27,480 --> 01:02:29,000
You're saying this is a switch?

1952
01:02:29,340 --> 01:02:31,340
(Possible door switch found)

1953
01:02:31,640 --> 01:02:32,240
Twist it.

1954
01:02:32,240 --> 01:02:33,160
Twist it. Come on.

1955
01:02:33,340 --> 01:02:34,260
(Backs away)

1956
01:02:34,340 --> 01:02:35,960
(Backing out)

1957
01:02:35,960 --> 01:02:36,400
I don't want to.

1958
01:02:36,400 --> 01:02:37,240
I'll do it.

1959
01:02:37,240 --> 01:02:37,960
(He's grown)

1960
01:02:37,960 --> 01:02:38,440
Come on.

1961
01:02:39,040 --> 01:02:40,720
Okay. Three, two, one.

1962
01:02:42,220 --> 01:02:45,540
(Home by green waters and hills, hearts
in a gentle spring breeze)

1963
01:02:49,640 --> 01:02:50,720
(Night vision mode)
Don't scare me, okay?

1964
01:02:52,120 --> 01:02:53,800
Does anyone have a Lights On Card?

1965
01:02:53,800 --> 01:02:55,160
No Lights On Card.

1966
01:02:55,160 --> 01:02:55,960
Only a Lights Off Card.

1967
01:02:55,960 --> 01:02:57,200
I have a Disguise Card.

1968
01:02:57,200 --> 01:02:58,440
Fine. No Lights On Card.

1969
01:02:58,440 --> 01:02:59,320
Then I'm not going in yet.

1970
01:02:59,320 --> 01:03:00,120
(Strategic retreat)

1971
01:03:00,120 --> 01:03:01,080
Can Ding walk?

1972
01:03:01,080 --> 01:03:02,160
I can't walk.

1973
01:03:02,160 --> 01:03:04,080
Then should I clear the way, guys?

1974
01:03:04,080 --> 01:03:05,720
(The only tank here)
Of course. You have to.

1975
01:03:06,880 --> 01:03:08,040
(The value of the "only tank")
I'll open this door.

1976
01:03:08,040 --> 01:03:09,200
If there's no danger,

1977
01:03:09,200 --> 01:03:09,960
I'll call you over.

1978
01:03:09,960 --> 01:03:10,400
Okay?

1979
01:03:10,460 --> 01:03:11,300
(Iron tank mode)

1980
01:03:11,300 --> 01:03:13,080
(This segment contains scary content.
Minors should watch with a guardian)

1981
01:03:13,080 --> 01:03:15,080
No one's here. Let's move forward.

1982
01:03:15,080 --> 01:03:16,360
I'm the only one up front, guys.

1983
01:03:16,360 --> 01:03:16,640
Let's go.

1984
01:03:17,020 --> 01:03:19,020
(Shield activated)

1985
01:03:19,040 --> 01:03:20,320
Is something moving?

1986
01:03:20,320 --> 01:03:21,040
It's fine. I'll go.

1987
01:03:21,100 --> 01:03:22,620
(Pathfinder)

1988
01:03:25,060 --> 01:03:26,700
(Fearless)

1989
01:03:26,880 --> 01:03:27,520
Listen to me.

1990
01:03:27,520 --> 01:03:28,080
Here's the plan.

1991
01:03:28,080 --> 01:03:29,120
I'll stay in front.

1992
01:03:29,120 --> 01:03:30,040
You guys follow me.

1993
01:03:30,040 --> 01:03:31,280
Just move forward.

1994
01:03:31,280 --> 01:03:32,320
I'm still ahead of you.

1995
01:03:33,300 --> 01:03:34,460
(Shield activated)

1996
01:03:34,480 --> 01:03:34,880
How about this?

1997
01:03:34,880 --> 01:03:35,720
Whose hand is this?

1998
01:03:35,720 --> 01:03:35,960
Okay.

1999
01:03:36,280 --> 01:03:37,080
Stay about

2000
01:03:37,080 --> 01:03:38,400
two arm lengths from me, okay?

2001
01:03:38,400 --> 01:03:40,040
(Pathfinder)
Of course. You have to.

2002
01:03:40,040 --> 01:03:40,840
Okay.

2003
01:03:40,840 --> 01:03:42,240
Keep your hand on your chest. Careful.

2004
01:03:42,240 --> 01:03:43,480
Keep him in the middle.

2005
01:03:43,480 --> 01:03:44,360
I know. I've got him.

2006
01:03:45,680 --> 01:03:46,720
Fine. I'll go last.

2007
01:03:46,720 --> 01:03:48,320
Okay. Let Ning take the back.

2008
01:04:03,140 --> 01:04:04,500
(Memorial)

2009
01:04:04,520 --> 01:04:05,360
Why's it so dark?

2010
01:04:05,880 --> 01:04:06,920
This is so scary.

2011
01:04:08,120 --> 01:04:08,960
Does someone have

2012
01:04:09,760 --> 01:04:11,040
a bell on their hand?

2013
01:04:11,240 --> 01:04:12,160
It's mine. It's on me.

2014
01:04:12,580 --> 01:04:14,780
(Entering one by one)

2015
01:04:16,780 --> 01:04:20,500
(Eyes shut, observing)

2016
01:04:22,320 --> 01:04:23,520
Don't mess around. Don't scare me.

2017
01:04:24,180 --> 01:04:25,020
(It's okay)

2018
01:04:25,020 --> 01:04:25,800
(Holds on)

2019
01:04:25,800 --> 01:04:26,520
Come on.

2020
01:04:27,500 --> 01:04:29,420
(Bro)

2021
01:04:29,880 --> 01:04:31,160
Is this some kind of formation?

2022
01:04:31,160 --> 01:04:31,620
(Secretly curious)

2023
01:04:31,620 --> 01:04:33,540
(Looking around)

2024
01:04:34,360 --> 01:04:35,640
This looks like a mourning hall.

2025
01:04:35,640 --> 01:04:36,320
I looked back.

2026
01:04:36,320 --> 01:04:37,800
There's a "memorial" sign.

2027
01:04:38,200 --> 01:04:39,560
Memorial. Like for mourning.

2028
01:04:39,560 --> 01:04:41,320
(Memorial)

2029
01:04:41,320 --> 01:04:43,480
Did you look at the door
when you came in?

2030
01:04:43,480 --> 01:04:45,120
"Chivalry" and "Manor" were separated.

2031
01:04:45,560 --> 01:04:46,360
A mortuary.

2032
01:04:46,360 --> 01:04:47,240
(Chivalry Manor, mortuary)

2033
01:04:47,240 --> 01:04:49,200
(Night vision mode)
A mortuary is an ancient...

2034
01:04:49,200 --> 01:04:49,920
Morgue.

2035
01:04:49,920 --> 01:04:50,400
Right.

2036
01:04:51,820 --> 01:04:53,940
(Circling around)

2037
01:04:53,940 --> 01:04:59,300
(Holding bro tight)

2038
01:04:59,520 --> 01:05:00,040
I can't take this.

2039
01:05:00,600 --> 01:05:01,960
Where's your musket?

2040
01:05:01,960 --> 01:05:02,720
I didn't bring it.

2041
01:05:03,840 --> 01:05:04,840
Okay, calm down, guys.

2042
01:05:22,060 --> 01:05:24,100
(Why circle everyone for a ritual?)

2043
01:05:30,360 --> 01:05:31,240
It's making me hot.

2044
01:05:31,240 --> 01:05:32,600
(What ritual is this heated?)

2045
01:05:32,600 --> 01:05:33,160
Kinda hot.

2046
01:05:48,240 --> 01:05:49,240
How did you get in?

2047
01:05:50,700 --> 01:05:54,500
(Let me catch my breath first)

2048
01:05:56,240 --> 01:05:57,760
Ning Waver.

2049
01:05:59,180 --> 01:06:01,180
(Why does he know Ning Waver?)

2050
01:06:01,200 --> 01:06:02,480
Little Ning Waver.

2051
01:06:04,320 --> 01:06:05,520
(Nice to meet you)
Yes. And you are?

2052
01:06:05,520 --> 01:06:06,440
You've got the nerve to come.

2053
01:06:08,640 --> 01:06:10,200
Remember what you did?

2054
01:06:10,260 --> 01:06:11,840
(He really doesn't)

2055
01:06:11,880 --> 01:06:13,240
Let me introduce myself.

2056
01:06:13,240 --> 01:06:14,160
My name is

2057
01:06:15,480 --> 01:06:16,880
Junzi Ruyu.

2058
01:06:17,960 --> 01:06:19,240
So that's the "Jun".

2059
01:06:19,240 --> 01:06:19,920
Yes.

2060
01:06:19,920 --> 01:06:20,840
(Junzi Ruyu, played by He Wenjun)

2061
01:06:20,840 --> 01:06:22,840
I'm the second senior of Shi Damen.

2062
01:06:24,800 --> 01:06:26,480
Then I also had a second senior brother.

2063
01:06:26,480 --> 01:06:27,800
His name was Junzi Ruyu.

2064
01:06:27,800 --> 01:06:30,200
But Junzi Ruyu was very mysterious.

2065
01:06:30,200 --> 01:06:31,560
After I returned to Shi Damen,

2066
01:06:31,560 --> 01:06:33,120
he never once showed up.

2067
01:06:33,120 --> 01:06:35,560
Ke, did you get the medicine?

2068
01:06:35,560 --> 01:06:35,920
I did.

2069
01:06:35,920 --> 01:06:36,640
Feeling better?

2070
01:06:37,140 --> 01:06:38,280
(Med-meds, check it out)

2071
01:06:38,280 --> 01:06:38,800
What medicine?

2072
01:06:38,960 --> 01:06:40,600
Junzi Ruyu kept sending me tonics.

2073
01:06:41,000 --> 01:06:42,360
I took a medicine

2074
01:06:42,880 --> 01:06:43,840
that can make

2075
01:06:43,840 --> 01:06:45,840
all your muscles and bones go limp.

2076
01:06:46,360 --> 01:06:48,400
It also drains your power
and inner strength.

2077
01:06:50,080 --> 01:06:50,960
You're Second Senior.

2078
01:06:50,960 --> 01:06:52,720
Did you know he used to be First Senior?

2079
01:06:52,720 --> 01:06:53,760
Of course I did.

2080
01:06:53,760 --> 01:06:57,000
Then what do you think
of him and Lord Tui doing...

2081
01:06:57,000 --> 01:06:58,000
All that dirty work?

2082
01:06:58,000 --> 01:06:58,440
Right.

2083
01:06:58,440 --> 01:06:59,800
(Shady business)

2084
01:06:59,800 --> 01:07:01,880
If Master knew what you did,

2085
01:07:01,880 --> 01:07:03,440
he'd be mad enough to sit up straight.

2086
01:07:03,800 --> 01:07:06,160
After Master died,
I returned to Tui City to find you.

2087
01:07:09,680 --> 01:07:10,760
I saw Lord Tui

2088
01:07:10,760 --> 01:07:12,200
take you to Chivalry Manor.

2089
01:07:12,200 --> 01:07:13,600
I watched from outside the wall,

2090
01:07:13,600 --> 01:07:15,080
waiting for a chance to save you.

2091
01:07:15,080 --> 01:07:16,240
But then,

2092
01:07:16,240 --> 01:07:17,440
you called him Father

2093
01:07:17,440 --> 01:07:18,960
and took him as your godfather.

2094
01:07:19,880 --> 01:07:20,800
Since then,

2095
01:07:20,800 --> 01:07:23,000
you became Lord Tui's lapdog son.

2096
01:07:23,000 --> 01:07:23,960
You've done every bad thing.

2097
01:07:28,580 --> 01:07:29,490
(Ning Waver identity summary)

2098
01:07:29,490 --> 01:07:30,800
(Related person: Junzi Ruyu.
Impression of Ning: lapdog son)

2099
01:07:30,820 --> 01:07:31,900
(Event related to Ning:
saw Ning take a villain as his father)

2100
01:07:31,920 --> 01:07:33,520
Why are you here?

2101
01:07:34,480 --> 01:07:35,280
Why am I here?

2102
01:07:35,880 --> 01:07:36,040
Yes.

2103
01:07:36,040 --> 01:07:37,240
Why did you show up here?

2104
01:07:38,400 --> 01:07:39,440
This is a mourning hall.

2105
01:07:39,440 --> 01:07:39,720
Did you notice?

2106
01:07:39,720 --> 01:07:39,960
Yes.

2107
01:07:39,960 --> 01:07:40,770
(Memorial)
I noticed.

2108
01:07:40,920 --> 01:07:42,240
I came in through the back door.

2109
01:07:42,760 --> 01:07:43,040
Back door?

2110
01:07:43,040 --> 01:07:44,000
There's a back door here?

2111
01:07:44,200 --> 01:07:44,960
Where does it lead?

2112
01:07:45,960 --> 01:07:48,320
This whole Chivalry Manor...

2113
01:07:48,320 --> 01:07:51,580
(There are still unexplored areas)

2114
01:07:51,600 --> 01:07:53,440
A lot of kids in Tui City
have gone missing.

2115
01:07:54,240 --> 01:07:54,880
Who did it?

2116
01:07:55,560 --> 01:07:56,480
Lord Tui did.

2117
01:07:56,480 --> 01:07:57,080
Right.

2118
01:07:57,080 --> 01:07:57,680
I saw it.

2119
01:07:58,440 --> 01:08:00,080
And then I...

2120
01:08:00,080 --> 01:08:02,360
My crush is named Yan Reason.

2121
01:08:02,880 --> 01:08:03,960
I know. My bestie.

2122
01:08:03,960 --> 01:08:04,840
I came here

2123
01:08:04,840 --> 01:08:05,880
because I need to find

2124
01:08:05,880 --> 01:08:07,520
Yan Reason.

2125
01:08:07,520 --> 01:08:09,120
She came here to save the kids,

2126
01:08:09,120 --> 01:08:10,200
then she disappeared too.

2127
01:08:10,200 --> 01:08:12,100
(Yan Reason vanished
while saving the kids)

2128
01:08:12,360 --> 01:08:13,680
She came in to save the kids.

2129
01:08:13,680 --> 01:08:15,280
I stayed outside to back her up.

2130
01:08:15,280 --> 01:08:17,000
But she never came out.

2131
01:08:17,000 --> 01:08:18,430
So I snuck in through the back door.

2132
01:08:18,430 --> 01:08:19,720
Then she was gone too.

2133
01:08:19,720 --> 01:08:20,720
The kids were gone too.

2134
01:08:20,720 --> 01:08:22,680
Only these rotting bodies were left.

2135
01:08:22,680 --> 01:08:25,120
The kids' deaths looked really strange.

2136
01:08:25,120 --> 01:08:26,390
Their bodies were covered in sores.

2137
01:08:26,390 --> 01:08:29,140
(Why were the kids' bodies
covered in sores?)

2138
01:08:29,160 --> 01:08:30,840
Now we have another key clue.

2139
01:08:30,840 --> 01:08:32,120
What's the logic here?

2140
01:08:32,120 --> 01:08:34,840
It means he had a motive to kill too.

2141
01:08:34,860 --> 01:08:35,620
Why?

2142
01:08:35,620 --> 01:08:36,310
(Ning Waver suspects Junzi Ruyu
also had a motive)

2143
01:08:36,310 --> 01:08:36,680
Right.

2144
01:08:36,680 --> 01:08:37,160
Why?

2145
01:08:37,430 --> 01:08:38,120
Right.

2146
01:08:38,640 --> 01:08:39,760
Exactly.

2147
01:08:39,760 --> 01:08:40,240
Why?

2148
01:08:40,240 --> 01:08:41,470
You knew I took a villain as my father.

2149
01:08:41,470 --> 01:08:42,310
So you'd hate me too.

2150
01:08:42,310 --> 01:08:44,000
Lord Tui hurt these kids.

2151
01:08:44,000 --> 01:08:45,160
So you'd hate him too.

2152
01:08:45,160 --> 01:08:45,960
Right.

2153
01:08:46,540 --> 01:08:47,230
(Junzi Ruyu's motive)

2154
01:08:47,230 --> 01:08:48,370
(Against Ning Waver: he saw Ning side
with evil and wanted to cut him down)

2155
01:08:48,380 --> 01:08:49,340
(Against Lord Tui: he saw Tui
hurt children and wanted justice)

2156
01:08:49,470 --> 01:08:50,000
One more thing.

2157
01:08:50,000 --> 01:08:52,200
Inside this door,

2158
01:08:52,200 --> 01:08:53,160
when I went in earlier,

2159
01:08:53,160 --> 01:08:54,880
I found that
there seemed to be a major clue inside.

2160
01:08:55,380 --> 01:08:57,580
(What other secret is behind the door?)

2161
01:08:57,600 --> 01:08:58,640
Then why don't you go in first?

2162
01:08:58,920 --> 01:08:59,160
Yeah.

2163
01:08:59,160 --> 01:09:00,000
Then we'll follow you in.

2164
01:09:00,000 --> 01:09:01,470
