01:17:24,320 --> 01:17:25,160
I can find it.

2438
01:17:25,800 --> 01:17:27,360
If it's not over there,
walk toward the light,

2439
01:17:27,360 --> 01:17:27,720
Ding.

2440
01:17:30,640 --> 01:17:31,360
I see it.

2441
01:17:38,320 --> 01:17:38,880
You see it?

2442
01:17:39,920 --> 01:17:41,080
It's on that shelf, right?

2443
01:17:42,160 --> 01:17:42,600
The doll.

2444
01:17:42,960 --> 01:17:44,040
Okay. We found the doll.

2445
01:17:44,040 --> 01:17:45,000
(Got the doll)
What about the food?

2446
01:17:45,000 --> 01:17:45,720
It's hanging over there.

2447
01:17:46,520 --> 01:17:47,160
What about the food?

2448
01:17:49,120 --> 01:17:50,480
Found the food too.

2449
01:17:51,480 --> 01:17:53,000
I found a letter.

2450
01:17:53,840 --> 01:17:55,000
Bring that back too.

2451
01:17:55,520 --> 01:17:57,560
But it's tied up there.
I can't get it off.

2452
01:17:59,320 --> 01:18:00,400
I can't pull it off.

2453
01:18:02,220 --> 01:18:05,820
(I'm here)

2454
01:18:07,920 --> 01:18:08,520
This is what he eats.

2455
01:18:11,640 --> 01:18:12,760
I really can't pull it off.

2456
01:18:12,760 --> 01:18:14,000
It's not like I'm not trying.

2457
01:18:14,540 --> 01:18:17,140
(The big brothers are here)

2458
01:18:17,160 --> 01:18:18,520
Take this down.

2459
01:18:18,520 --> 01:18:19,280
I'll do it.

2460
01:18:21,600 --> 01:18:21,840
This...

2461
01:18:21,840 --> 01:18:22,480
Bite it.

2462
01:18:23,800 --> 01:18:24,800
Watch your teeth.

2463
01:18:25,960 --> 01:18:27,560
They bit it off with their teeth?

2464
01:18:28,000 --> 01:18:28,560
Let's go.

2465
01:18:29,400 --> 01:18:30,480
Did you get it?

2466
01:18:30,480 --> 01:18:31,120
Got it.

2467
01:18:31,120 --> 01:18:31,600
Give it to me.

2468
01:18:31,600 --> 01:18:32,320
Okay.

2469
01:18:32,320 --> 01:18:32,840
Here.

2470
01:18:36,920 --> 01:18:38,000
This doll is mine.

2471
01:18:38,000 --> 01:18:39,960
But this coin pouch isn't.

2472
01:18:39,960 --> 01:18:40,640
Take it back.

2473
01:18:41,480 --> 01:18:42,480
Got it. It's in my hand.

2474
01:18:42,480 --> 01:18:44,960
Okay. You can leave now.

2475
01:18:46,680 --> 01:18:47,960
Okay. Careful.

2476
01:18:51,960 --> 01:18:52,920
Come on.

2477
01:18:53,680 --> 01:18:55,560
Come on. Out. Who's this?

2478
01:18:55,560 --> 01:18:56,560
You.

2479
01:18:56,560 --> 01:18:57,120
(Still shaken)
Go.

2480
01:18:57,120 --> 01:18:57,920
There are two.

2481
01:18:57,920 --> 01:18:59,000
Me.

2482
01:18:59,000 --> 01:18:59,480
Let's go.

2483
01:18:59,480 --> 01:19:02,760
Let's take the evidence
to the inn and check it out.

2484
01:19:02,760 --> 01:19:03,560
Let's go.

2485
01:19:10,800 --> 01:19:12,560
This place would be scary at night.

2486
01:19:12,560 --> 01:19:14,760
(Figured out the system)
At night, it's seriously scary.

2487
01:19:14,760 --> 01:19:15,920
It's fine now.

2488
01:19:16,060 --> 01:19:17,320
(Casual stroll in the daytime)
How does it feel?

2489
01:19:17,320 --> 01:19:18,600
(Full meltdown at night)
Kind of dead inside.

2490
01:19:18,640 --> 01:19:19,120
Seems okay to me.

2491
01:19:19,120 --> 01:19:19,520
Not bad.

2492
01:19:20,080 --> 01:19:21,920
At least he made it over there.

2493
01:19:21,920 --> 01:19:23,080
No. You know why?

2494
01:19:23,080 --> 01:19:25,000
Because he could hear our voices.

2495
01:19:25,000 --> 01:19:25,160
Yeah.

2496
01:19:25,160 --> 01:19:26,480
It's okay when we're with him.

2497
01:19:26,480 --> 01:19:28,060
(Where there are friends, it's safe)

2498
01:19:28,440 --> 01:19:28,840
Come on.

2499
01:19:29,280 --> 01:19:29,920
Time to deduce.

2500
01:19:29,920 --> 01:19:31,220
(Truth Inn)

2501
01:19:34,840 --> 01:19:36,160
We're finally home.

2502
01:19:36,780 --> 01:19:37,580
(Unlock the detective team's
best moments early)

2503
01:19:37,580 --> 01:19:38,340
(At every Tuesday noon,
Dungeon Unlocking)

2504
01:19:38,340 --> 01:19:40,300
(Face card under maintenance)

2505
01:19:42,700 --> 01:19:44,860
(Found another new toy)

2506
01:19:46,900 --> 01:19:49,900
(Loves recreating bugs)

2507
01:19:50,960 --> 01:19:51,640
Okay.

2508
01:19:51,640 --> 01:19:52,160
Come on.

2509
01:19:52,160 --> 01:19:52,400
Go back.

2510
01:19:52,400 --> 01:19:53,780
(Playtime's over. Back to the case)
Back to that room.

2511
01:19:53,800 --> 01:19:54,720
Let's use this.

2512
01:19:55,180 --> 01:19:56,640
(Good stuff must be shared)
Okay.

2513
01:19:56,680 --> 01:19:58,040
Next time, get food.

2514
01:19:58,040 --> 01:19:59,400
Not that kind of toy.

2515
01:19:59,580 --> 01:20:00,860
(Restocking together)

2516
01:20:01,400 --> 01:20:02,920
We know who did it.

2517
01:20:02,920 --> 01:20:03,680
Two killers.

2518
01:20:03,680 --> 01:20:04,640
(Truth Supply Station drops randomly)
Stop eating.

2519
01:20:04,640 --> 01:20:05,520
(Snack chat mode. Stay tuned.)
We know it's you two.

2520
01:20:05,520 --> 01:20:06,720
You two worked together.

2521
01:20:08,020 --> 01:20:10,340
(Food and toys, both secured)

2522
01:20:11,280 --> 01:20:12,960
After what we just went through,

2523
01:20:12,960 --> 01:20:14,680
one important thing is

2524
01:20:14,680 --> 01:20:16,520
this is a locked-room murder.

2525
01:20:16,520 --> 01:20:16,960
Exactly.

2526
01:20:17,480 --> 01:20:19,240
(Locked-room murder)
How did the killer get out?

2527
01:20:19,240 --> 01:20:20,040
Right now,

2528
01:20:20,040 --> 01:20:21,240
there are two possibilities.

2529
01:20:21,240 --> 01:20:23,880
Someone who knows
the manor well might know

2530
01:20:23,880 --> 01:20:25,840
(Someone who knows the manor)
about the secret door.

2531
01:20:25,840 --> 01:20:27,560
I came in through the back door.

2532
01:20:27,960 --> 01:20:28,240
Back door?

2533
01:20:28,240 --> 01:20:29,240
There's a back door here?

2534
01:20:29,240 --> 01:20:30,000
Where does it lead?

2535
01:20:31,000 --> 01:20:33,360
To the whole manor.

2536
01:20:33,460 --> 01:20:36,060
(Killer escape route 1: Back door)

2537
01:20:36,080 --> 01:20:38,480
But an outsider probably
wouldn't know the layout.

2538
01:20:38,480 --> 01:20:39,880
They'd know about this window.

2539
01:20:39,880 --> 01:20:42,420
(Killer escape route 2:
the window, for outsiders)

2540
01:20:42,440 --> 01:20:45,040
(Meeting Hall blueprint)
That window can only open outward.

2541
01:20:45,480 --> 01:20:47,480
(This window only pushes outward)
So no one could've come in through it.

2542
01:20:47,480 --> 01:20:48,300
(Meeting Hall window: exit only, )

2543
01:20:48,720 --> 01:20:50,400
But when we went in,

2544
01:20:50,400 --> 01:20:52,120
there were a lot
of bamboo slips on the floor.

2545
01:20:52,180 --> 01:20:53,760
(Many bamboo slips were scattered
on the Meeting Hall floor)

2546
01:20:53,760 --> 01:20:54,520
Which means

2547
01:20:54,520 --> 01:20:55,840
the killer may have left through there.

2548
01:20:55,840 --> 01:20:57,000
Because they used the bamboo slips.

2549
01:20:57,000 --> 01:20:58,280
They probably made some kind of device.

2550
01:20:58,280 --> 01:20:58,640
Right.

2551
01:20:58,700 --> 01:21:00,820
(Theory: The killer used the bamboo-slip
device to escape through the window)

2552
01:21:00,900 --> 01:21:02,260
(Escape route 1: Back door. Someone
who knows Chivalry Manor)

2553
01:21:02,260 --> 01:21:03,540
(Escape route 2: Window. Someone
from outside Chivalry Manor)

2554
01:21:03,560 --> 01:21:04,280
So I think

2555
01:21:04,280 --> 01:21:05,000
this person

2556
01:21:05,000 --> 01:21:06,480
was already hiding inside

2557
01:21:06,480 --> 01:21:08,000
before they entered the room.

2558
01:21:08,000 --> 01:21:09,320
(Yang's theory: The killer hid
in the Meeting Hall beforehand)

2559
01:21:09,320 --> 01:21:09,960
No.

2560
01:21:09,960 --> 01:21:11,640
Everything he saw yesterday

2561
01:21:11,640 --> 01:21:12,600
really happened.

2562
01:21:13,080 --> 01:21:14,920
He saw someone appear
and chased after him.

2563
01:21:14,920 --> 01:21:15,880
Chased after him.

2564
01:21:15,900 --> 01:21:19,500
(Brain replaying)

2565
01:21:19,760 --> 01:21:20,040
Wait.

2566
01:21:20,040 --> 01:21:21,960
There was a blank spot in my memory.

2567
01:21:25,360 --> 01:21:27,320
(Chivalry Manor)
I saw from far away that

2568
01:21:27,320 --> 01:21:29,160
after he carried you inside,

2569
01:21:29,160 --> 01:21:30,560
your dad

2570
01:21:30,560 --> 01:21:32,440
shouted, "Don't hurt my son"!

2571
01:21:32,440 --> 01:21:33,160
Then he ran in.

2572
01:21:34,280 --> 01:21:35,880
Hurry! The young master is in danger!

2573
01:21:36,200 --> 01:21:38,160
Don't hurt my son!

2574
01:21:38,640 --> 01:21:40,720
I hadn't reached the door yet.

2575
01:21:40,720 --> 01:21:42,040
(Chivalry Manor)
When I got to the door,

2576
01:21:42,040 --> 01:21:43,200
(He Ha didn't see it)
the man in black was gone.

2577
01:21:43,200 --> 01:21:44,160
(How did the killer
and Ning Waver enter Chivalry Manor?)

2578
01:21:44,160 --> 01:21:45,160
The door was closed too.

2579
01:21:45,160 --> 01:21:46,040
It was locked too.

2580
01:21:46,920 --> 01:21:49,280
Then why would they

2581
01:21:49,280 --> 01:21:50,600
lock the room to fight inside?

2582
01:21:50,600 --> 01:21:53,660
(Why lock the door?)

2583
01:21:54,320 --> 01:21:54,920
I...

2584
01:21:55,480 --> 01:21:56,120
Didn't I die?

2585
01:21:56,120 --> 01:21:57,120
Why am I alive again?

2586
01:21:57,120 --> 01:21:58,360
That's the biggest question.

2587
01:21:58,360 --> 01:21:58,800
The biggest question.

2588
01:21:58,800 --> 01:21:59,120
Right.

2589
01:21:59,700 --> 01:22:00,900
(Questions so far:
How did the killer escape?)

2590
01:22:00,900 --> 01:22:02,260
(Why lock the room to fight?)

2591
01:22:02,260 --> 01:22:03,460
(Why did Ning Waver come back to life?)

2592
01:22:03,800 --> 01:22:04,680
Let's check the ledger.

2593
01:22:05,560 --> 01:22:05,800
This...

2594
01:22:05,800 --> 01:22:06,440
Bite it.

2595
01:22:06,440 --> 01:22:07,760
(The ledger He bit off from Lord Tui)

2596
01:22:07,760 --> 01:22:08,760
Careful with your teeth.

2597
01:22:08,760 --> 01:22:10,560
Year 260 of Tui.

2598
01:22:10,560 --> 01:22:12,200
Lord Tui's private ledger.

2599
01:22:12,300 --> 01:22:14,940
(Year 260 of Tui,
Lord Tui's private ledger)

2600
01:22:14,940 --> 01:22:16,820
(The ledger just bitten off)

2601
01:22:17,600 --> 01:22:20,320
To help poor children and commoners,

2602
01:22:20,320 --> 01:22:22,720
we must rely on merchants for funds.

2603
01:22:22,720 --> 01:22:23,760
He wanted people to donate money.

2604
01:22:23,760 --> 01:22:24,860
(Lord Tui raised donations for children)

2605
01:22:25,120 --> 01:22:26,520
From January 1, Year 258

2606
01:22:26,520 --> 01:22:29,000
to January 1, Year 260,

2607
01:22:29,000 --> 01:22:31,280
Shi Damen won people's hearts

2608
01:22:31,280 --> 01:22:32,280
through chivalry.

2609
01:22:33,000 --> 01:22:35,240
After I became city lord,

2610
01:22:35,240 --> 01:22:37,200
I used the name of chivalry

2611
01:22:37,200 --> 01:22:40,440
to collect huge donations
from Tui City's merchants.

2612
01:22:40,440 --> 01:22:44,080
If anyone refused, I sent Ning
to threaten them by force.

2613
01:22:44,140 --> 01:22:45,740
(Shi Damen won people's
hearts through chivalry)

2614
01:22:45,740 --> 01:22:47,460
(Lord Tui used chivalry as an excuse
to force donations)

2615
01:22:47,480 --> 01:22:49,520
All the donations went into my pocket!

2616
01:22:49,520 --> 01:22:50,280
He was so happy.

2617
01:22:50,280 --> 01:22:51,360
His face was full of money.

2618
01:22:51,820 --> 01:22:52,680
(Lord Tui pocketed all the donations)

2619
01:22:52,680 --> 01:22:53,600
After he became city lord,

2620
01:22:53,600 --> 01:22:55,040
he started doing evil.

2621
01:22:55,040 --> 01:22:55,360
Right.

2622
01:22:55,360 --> 01:22:56,680
Then the next part.

2623
01:22:56,680 --> 01:22:59,680
He put some kind of poison
on the vegetables.

2624
01:22:59,700 --> 01:23:02,500
(Poison)

2625
01:23:02,520 --> 01:23:03,800
Serving soup to the public.

2626
01:23:03,800 --> 01:23:05,760
Children only. Free to claim.

2627
01:23:05,760 --> 01:23:07,640
March 1, Year 260.

2628
01:23:07,640 --> 01:23:10,320
The merchants urged me to carry out
the charity project.

2629
01:23:11,120 --> 01:23:13,160
Luckily, from my benefactor...

2630
01:23:13,450 --> 01:23:14,960
(Lord Tui has a benefactor behind him)
He has a benefactor.

2631
01:23:14,960 --> 01:23:16,680
I got a secret medicine
from a benefactor.

2632
01:23:17,120 --> 01:23:19,800
It can make spoiled ingredients
look fresh.

2633
01:23:19,860 --> 01:23:22,140
(The secret medicine makes spoiled food
look fresh)

2634
01:23:22,480 --> 01:23:23,840
Did you use this on your buns?

2635
01:23:23,840 --> 01:23:24,320
Your buns are like that.

2636
01:23:24,320 --> 01:23:24,960
(Jin Thrifty's buns)
Buns?

2637
01:23:24,960 --> 01:23:26,360
(Did she use preservative water too?)
I wouldn't use that stuff.

2638
01:23:26,360 --> 01:23:28,520
I make mine with love and sincerity.

2639
01:23:31,780 --> 01:23:33,660
(Kind of cute)

2640
01:23:33,680 --> 01:23:35,440
No one in this world

2641
01:23:35,440 --> 01:23:37,120
is easier to fool than children.

2642
01:23:37,340 --> 01:23:39,020
(Fooling children?)

2643
01:23:39,040 --> 01:23:41,320
They only see fresh-looking food.

2644
01:23:41,320 --> 01:23:43,080
They can't tell if it's rotten.

2645
01:23:43,480 --> 01:23:46,400
Besides, these poor children
are worthless.

2646
01:23:46,960 --> 01:23:48,400
Why waste good rice on them?

2647
01:23:48,400 --> 01:23:51,080
It's pure profit. Why not do it?

2648
01:23:51,880 --> 01:23:53,880
(Poisoned charity food)
He added medicine to fake freshness.

2649
01:23:53,880 --> 01:23:54,720
(Fake charity, real harm)
Then he fed it to them.

2650
01:23:54,720 --> 01:23:56,560
That way, he can still look charitable.

2651
01:23:57,040 --> 01:23:57,880
And earn a good reputation.

2652
01:23:57,880 --> 01:23:59,180
(Lord Tui's charity was a show, using
preservative soup to fool the people)

2653
01:23:59,680 --> 01:24:00,560
A hypocrite.

2654
01:24:00,560 --> 01:24:01,720
I told you he was bad.

2655
01:24:01,720 --> 01:24:02,840
He's a hypocrite.

2656
01:24:02,840 --> 01:24:03,120
Right.

2657
01:24:04,240 --> 01:24:04,960
He deserved to die.

2658
01:24:07,040 --> 01:24:07,640
He deserved it.

2659
01:24:08,600 --> 01:24:09,320
He deserved it.

2660
01:24:09,320 --> 01:24:10,080
The killer.

2661
01:24:10,080 --> 01:24:11,200
Killer, come out. You did great.

2662
01:24:11,200 --> 01:24:12,080
(Detective mode on.
Time to bluff the killer)

2663
01:24:12,080 --> 01:24:12,840
The killer.

2664
01:24:12,840 --> 01:24:13,960
(Killer)
Killer, come out. You did great.

2665
01:24:14,880 --> 01:24:15,480
Really great.

2666
01:24:15,480 --> 01:24:16,740
(Killer)

2667
01:24:16,960 --> 01:24:18,800
(Searching high and low for the killer)
Killer, come out. You did great.

2668
01:24:18,800 --> 01:24:19,400
Really great.

2669
01:24:19,400 --> 01:24:22,460
(Killer)

2670
01:24:22,480 --> 01:24:23,440
You think it's that easy

2671
01:24:23,440 --> 01:24:24,760
to trick someone into confessing?

2672
01:24:27,320 --> 01:24:28,480
Then they gave him an award

2673
01:24:28,480 --> 01:24:29,320
for benefiting the people.

2674
01:24:29,320 --> 01:24:31,360
Then the Chivalrous City Lord...

2675
01:24:31,360 --> 01:24:33,200
Everyone was fooled.

2676
01:24:33,400 --> 01:24:36,240
The merchants and people
of Tui City all praised him.

2677
01:24:36,240 --> 01:24:37,440
Few complained.

2678
01:24:37,880 --> 01:24:40,920
He sent Ning Waver
to threaten them by force.

2679
01:24:41,420 --> 01:24:43,980
(Ning Waver was involved too)

2680
01:24:44,000 --> 01:24:44,880
He made you threaten them.

2681
01:24:45,580 --> 01:24:46,560
(Lapdog)

2682
01:24:46,560 --> 01:24:46,840
Yes.

2683
01:24:46,840 --> 01:24:47,820
(Speechless)

2684
01:24:47,820 --> 01:24:48,820
(Ning the Lapdog)

2685
01:24:48,820 --> 01:24:50,060
(Ungrateful jerk)

2686
01:24:50,140 --> 01:24:52,100
(I lost my memory.
I don't know anything)

2687
01:24:53,740 --> 01:24:55,500
(Take my blade)

2688
01:24:57,360 --> 01:24:59,160
His amnesia gives him a free pass now.

2689
01:24:59,660 --> 01:25:00,980
(Fine, I'll let you off)

2690
01:25:01,880 --> 01:25:02,840
May 3.

2691
01:25:02,840 --> 01:25:04,360
The children who ate the spoiled soup

2692
01:25:04,360 --> 01:25:06,840
started vomiting and having diarrhea.

2693
01:25:06,840 --> 01:25:09,400
Some had deformities and rotting flesh.

2694
01:25:09,420 --> 01:25:12,140
(Same symptoms as the children
who ate Jin Thrifty's buns)

2695
01:25:12,160 --> 01:25:14,200
Jin Thrifty's meat buns

2696
01:25:14,200 --> 01:25:15,280
kept getting complaints.

2697
01:25:15,280 --> 01:25:16,400
It was a gift from above.

2698
01:25:16,400 --> 01:25:17,800
(The scapegoat)

2699
01:25:17,800 --> 01:25:18,800
May 5.

2700
01:25:18,800 --> 01:25:22,560
They made buns with rotten filling
laced with the secret drug

2701
01:25:22,560 --> 01:25:24,360
and slipped them into Jin Inn,

2702
01:25:24,360 --> 01:25:25,560
framing Jin.

2703
01:25:26,000 --> 01:25:27,840
(You made me take the fall)
So it was you guys.

2704
01:25:28,560 --> 01:25:29,000
I checked.

2705
01:25:29,000 --> 01:25:30,160
Her buns were fine.

2706
01:25:31,200 --> 01:25:32,480
They were just...

2707
01:25:32,540 --> 01:25:33,920
(Just nasty)

2708
01:25:33,920 --> 01:25:34,760
But

2709
01:25:34,760 --> 01:25:36,400
while everyone was complaining
about you,

2710
01:25:36,400 --> 01:25:38,320
he mixed in his fake buns.

2711
01:25:38,380 --> 01:25:39,860
(Theory: Lord Tui mixed
preservative-laced buns into Jin's buns)

2712
01:25:39,860 --> 01:25:40,320
(to frame her for the crime)

2713
01:25:40,320 --> 01:25:41,840
So she got the wrong idea about you.

2714
01:25:41,840 --> 01:25:45,160
The kids who ate the soup
started falling sick one after another.

2715
01:25:45,160 --> 01:25:46,840
It was about to get exposed.

2716
01:25:46,840 --> 01:25:49,800
I could use Tui City's

2717
01:25:49,800 --> 01:25:51,720
old ghost soldier legend
to get myself off the hook.

2718
01:25:52,280 --> 01:25:55,800
First, I ordered my men to move
the sick children

2719
01:25:55,800 --> 01:25:58,040
to the manor and hide them.

2720
01:25:58,600 --> 01:26:01,280
Second, frame Jin Thrifty

2721
01:26:01,280 --> 01:26:02,920
for using witchcraft to harm children

2722
01:26:02,920 --> 01:26:04,520
and raise ghost soldiers.

2723
01:26:04,520 --> 01:26:06,760
Third, send Ning to threaten her.

2724
01:26:07,560 --> 01:26:09,920
So all of Ning's actions

2725
01:26:09,920 --> 01:26:11,160
were under this

2726
01:26:11,160 --> 01:26:12,960
City Lord Tui's orders.

2727
01:26:12,960 --> 01:26:14,720
That explains why

2728
01:26:14,720 --> 01:26:15,520
he did all this.

2729
01:26:15,520 --> 01:26:18,120
He told you to leave right away
and look guilty running away.

2730
01:26:18,440 --> 01:26:20,280
The neck grabbing, the cheek pinching...

2731
01:26:20,280 --> 01:26:22,040
City Lord Tui told him to do it.

2732
01:26:22,040 --> 01:26:23,600
(So it wasn't because I'm pretty)
Pinching my cheeks?

2733
01:26:23,600 --> 01:26:24,280
Right.

2734
01:26:24,340 --> 01:26:27,340
(Theory: Ning Waver forced Jin Thrifty
to leave under Lord Tui's orders)

2735
01:26:27,360 --> 01:26:28,080
The shoe.

2736
01:26:28,080 --> 01:26:28,800
Let me see that shoe.

2737
01:26:29,720 --> 01:26:31,160
(Blood-stained embroidered shoe)
A bloody shoe.

2738
01:26:33,800 --> 01:26:34,400
Wait.

2739
01:26:34,400 --> 01:26:35,520
Isn't this that shoe?

2740
01:26:37,280 --> 01:26:37,760
You know...

2741
01:26:37,760 --> 01:26:39,640
The one that fighter wore.

2742
01:26:39,700 --> 01:26:42,420
(The exact same embroidered shoe)

2743
01:26:43,880 --> 01:26:44,480
Really?

2744
01:26:44,480 --> 01:26:44,960
Yeah!

2745
01:26:44,960 --> 01:26:45,520
Yan.

2746
01:26:46,220 --> 01:26:47,820
(Yan Reason's embroidered shoe)

2747
01:26:47,840 --> 01:26:48,360
Yan!

2748
01:26:48,880 --> 01:26:49,800
My best (friend).

2749
01:26:52,320 --> 01:26:52,720
Oh no.

2750
01:26:52,720 --> 01:26:53,840
(Did something happen to Yan Reason?)

2751
01:26:53,840 --> 01:26:54,720
There's blood on it.

2752
01:26:54,720 --> 01:26:55,880
That means she may have been killed.

2753
01:26:55,880 --> 01:26:57,080
She may have been killed, right?

2754
01:26:57,140 --> 01:27:01,780
(Yan Reason has already been killed?)

2755
01:27:02,880 --> 01:27:04,480
Why were you looking at her shoes?

2756
01:27:04,480 --> 01:27:05,720
Because they really looked pretty.

2757
01:27:06,880 --> 01:27:07,520
I saw them too.

2758
01:27:07,520 --> 01:27:08,320
They were really pretty.

2759
01:27:08,560 --> 01:27:08,800
Yeah.

2760
01:27:09,680 --> 01:27:10,600
The money pouch.

2761
01:27:12,400 --> 01:27:13,360
What's inside?

2762
01:27:14,120 --> 01:27:15,080
Let me check.

2763
01:27:15,920 --> 01:27:17,240
May 26.

2764
01:27:17,240 --> 01:27:18,760
I've confirmed

2765
01:27:18,760 --> 01:27:20,120
that the Qide Sword Jin Thrifty
planned to use

2766
01:27:20,120 --> 01:27:22,880
at the sword-viewing event is fake.

2767
01:27:23,240 --> 01:27:24,560
(Someone knew in advance)
It's fake.

2768
01:27:24,560 --> 01:27:26,760
(The Qide Sword in Jin's hands is fake)
Someone asked about your sword before.

2769
01:27:26,960 --> 01:27:28,720
Today, I happened to find

2770
01:27:28,720 --> 01:27:30,440
a mysterious person in a cloak,

2771
01:27:30,440 --> 01:27:31,720
with their face covered,

2772
01:27:31,720 --> 01:27:34,240
carrying the real Qide Sword
in the Ghost Market.

2773
01:27:34,240 --> 01:27:37,160
I also found that the mystery person
often goes in and out of

2774
01:27:37,160 --> 01:27:38,720
places with this mark.

2775
01:27:38,720 --> 01:27:39,480
There's a symbol here.

2776
01:27:41,560 --> 01:27:43,000
This symbol.

2777
01:27:43,320 --> 01:27:44,120
The Ghost Market symbol.

2778
01:27:44,120 --> 01:27:45,240
Yes, that's the one.

2779
01:27:45,300 --> 01:27:48,740
(What does Yan Reason
have to do with the Ghost Market?)

2780
01:27:48,760 --> 01:27:50,480
Looks like this is tied
to the Ghost Market too.

2781
01:27:50,540 --> 01:27:52,220
(Where's the Ghost Market?)

2782
01:27:52,240 --> 01:27:56,000
To enter the Ghost Market,
go to the dock at Xu hour.

2783
01:27:56,920 --> 01:27:59,160
Find the tree with lots of lanterns

2784
01:27:59,540 --> 01:28:01,220
(Lots of lanterns)

2785
01:28:01,340 --> 01:28:05,300
and red ropes tied around it.

2786
01:28:06,060 --> 01:28:09,220
Each person holds
three lit incense sticks

2787
01:28:09,220 --> 01:28:12,620
and bows to the tree
three times together.

2788
01:28:13,420 --> 01:28:15,420
Put the incense in the burner.

2789
01:28:15,420 --> 01:28:19,220
Then you can hear the passphrase once.

2790
01:28:19,480 --> 01:28:20,960
Remember it.

2791
01:28:20,960 --> 01:28:22,440
Shout the passphrase toward the river,

2792
01:28:22,440 --> 01:28:23,600
and you can go there.

2793
01:28:23,600 --> 01:28:24,040
We're done.

2794
01:28:24,520 --> 01:28:26,120
(Another nighttime activity)
Zi, Chou, Yin, Mao.

2795
01:28:26,600 --> 01:28:27,800
Is this even right?

2796
01:28:28,740 --> 01:28:30,060
(A bad omen)

2797
01:28:30,080 --> 01:28:30,600
Please note.

2798
01:28:30,600 --> 01:28:33,440
The passphrase can only be heard once.

2799
01:28:34,440 --> 01:28:36,280
So we're still in the human world?

2800
01:28:38,220 --> 01:28:39,780
(You can only go
to the Ghost Market at Xu hour)

2801
01:28:39,800 --> 01:28:41,000
(Truth Inn)
We haven't reached the Ghost Market yet.

2802
01:28:41,680 --> 01:28:43,120
Next, we're going into the Ghost Market.

2803
01:28:43,120 --> 01:28:44,720
This mystery person
has the real Qide Sword,

2804
01:28:44,720 --> 01:28:46,560
so we need to look in there.

2805
01:28:46,700 --> 01:28:49,100
(The real Qide Sword
is in the Ghost Market)

2806
01:28:49,120 --> 01:28:50,720
Whoever has the Qide Sword
is the killer.

2807
01:28:50,720 --> 01:28:52,080
So among us,

2808
01:28:52,080 --> 01:28:53,480
one person is the mystery person?

2809
01:28:53,920 --> 01:28:55,520
That's what it looks like for now.

2810
01:28:55,580 --> 01:28:57,220
(Theory: the mystery person
(the killer) is among the suspects)

2811
01:28:57,860 --> 01:29:06,340
(Who is the mystery person
with the real Qide Sword?)

2812
01:29:07,480 --> 01:29:09,120
Xu hour is here!

2813
01:29:10,480 --> 01:29:11,200
Let's head out.

2814
01:29:11,200 --> 01:29:11,640
Let's go.

2815
01:29:11,640 --> 01:29:12,480
It's time. Let's go.

2816
01:29:12,640 --> 01:29:14,440
I'll carry the incense for you.

2817
01:29:14,640 --> 01:29:15,640
Okay. Let's go.

2818
01:29:15,640 --> 01:29:16,080
Okay.

2819
01:29:17,240 --> 01:29:17,840
Hurry.

2820
01:29:18,280 --> 01:29:19,320
While it's still light out.

2821
01:29:20,040 --> 01:29:21,360
It'll be safer that way.

2822
01:29:22,040 --> 01:29:23,000
It's so pretty.

2823
01:29:23,680 --> 01:29:24,680
Blue Hour.

2824
01:29:26,400 --> 01:29:27,560
Let's find the dock.

2825
01:29:27,680 --> 01:29:28,960
Go to the marked spot.

2826
01:29:28,960 --> 01:29:29,880
Face the river.

2827
01:29:29,880 --> 01:29:31,000
Shout the secret phrase.

2828
01:29:31,720 --> 01:29:33,040
Your brain's so good.

2829
01:29:33,040 --> 01:29:34,040
I think that's it.

2830
01:29:34,040 --> 01:29:35,300
(Young brains really are different)

2831
01:29:37,320 --> 01:29:37,680
It's here.

2832
01:29:38,240 --> 01:29:39,640
This might be the dock.

2833
01:29:39,660 --> 01:29:41,900
(Dock)

2834
01:29:47,400 --> 01:29:48,200
It's here.

2835
01:29:48,200 --> 01:29:49,440
The tree with the red rope.

2836
01:30:01,600 --> 01:30:02,040
Here.

2837
01:30:02,400 --> 01:30:04,160
Light this stick of incense.

2838
01:30:08,440 --> 01:30:09,200
This one's ready.

2839
01:30:10,720 --> 01:30:11,800
No one's gonna pop out
of the ground, right?

2840
01:30:11,820 --> 01:30:13,160
(Uneasy)

2841
01:30:13,160 --> 01:30:14,040
No way, right?

2842
01:30:16,760 --> 01:30:17,960
Come on. Do we bow together?

2843
01:30:17,960 --> 01:30:19,120
Come on. Stand in a circle.

2844
01:30:28,040 --> 01:30:29,720
Let's become sworn siblings.

2845
01:30:29,720 --> 01:30:31,280
Share sweetness and death.

2846
01:30:31,800 --> 01:30:32,880
Share sweetness and death? No.

2847
01:30:32,880 --> 01:30:34,320
That's a bad deal for you.

2848
01:30:36,240 --> 01:30:37,160
I'm older.

2849
01:30:37,160 --> 01:30:37,880
It's not worth it for you.

2850
01:30:38,560 --> 01:30:39,720
We'll stay with you.

2851
01:30:41,320 --> 01:30:42,720
Share the good times.

2852
01:30:42,720 --> 01:30:44,720
Face the hard times together.

2853
01:30:44,720 --> 01:30:46,280
Come on. First bow.

2854
01:30:46,280 --> 01:30:47,280
To heaven and earth.

2855
01:30:54,960 --> 01:30:56,360
Second bow.

2856
01:30:56,360 --> 01:30:57,720
To our elders.

2857
01:31:03,680 --> 01:31:04,400
Siblings,

2858
01:31:04,400 --> 01:31:06,480
bow to each other.

2859
01:31:13,120 --> 01:31:14,400
May we solve this case.

2860
01:31:18,920 --> 01:31:19,360
There's a signal.

2861
01:31:26,000 --> 01:31:26,600
The light turned green.

2862
01:31:27,920 --> 01:31:28,840
An eerie green glow.

2863
01:32:12,920 --> 01:32:13,880
Okay. Who remembers it?

2864
01:32:15,160 --> 01:32:16,520
It kinda slipped out of my brain.

2865
01:32:16,520 --> 01:32:17,820
(Head empty)

2866
01:32:18,160 --> 01:32:18,760
I've already forgotten it.

2867
01:32:18,780 --> 01:32:19,900
(Head empty +1)

2868
01:32:20,220 --> 01:32:22,360
Teddy crackers, that's me.

2869
01:32:28,220 --> 01:32:29,540
(You memorized it too?)

2870
01:32:29,820 --> 01:32:31,660
I rush dumb through the sky.

2871
01:32:31,780 --> 01:32:34,340
Welcome my empty heart.

2872
01:32:35,500 --> 01:32:36,940
(Hahaha)

2873
01:32:37,060 --> 01:32:37,820
(Extra scenes 12 PM every Sat)

2874
01:32:37,840 --> 01:32:38,960
We two can just go hahaha.

2875
01:32:40,680 --> 01:32:41,320
Go down.

2876
01:32:43,680 --> 01:32:44,280
What does that mean?

2877
01:32:47,440 --> 01:32:48,240
Okay.

2878
01:32:48,240 --> 01:32:48,810
Come on.

2879
01:32:48,810 --> 01:32:50,890
Teddy crackers, that's me!

2880
01:32:58,240 --> 01:32:59,880
I rush dumb through the sky.

2881
01:33:00,020 --> 01:33:03,070
Welcome my empty heart.

2882
01:33:03,100 --> 01:33:05,900
(Trying to behave group)
Hahaha!

2883
01:33:06,300 --> 01:33:08,380
(Gen Z going primal)

2884
01:33:08,460 --> 01:33:10,220
(Fully possessed group)

2885
01:33:24,480 --> 01:33:25,200
What's going on?

2886
01:33:25,700 --> 01:33:27,180
(The lake stays totally still)

2887
01:33:29,020 --> 01:33:30,900
(Where did it go wrong?)

2888
01:33:31,120 --> 01:33:31,760
Let's do it again.

2889
01:33:33,200 --> 01:33:33,840
Let's go over it again.

2890
01:33:35,120 --> 01:33:38,160
We have a Restore Card.

2891
01:33:38,440 --> 01:33:39,320
I have a card.

2892
01:33:39,320 --> 01:33:39,760
What card?

2893
01:33:40,760 --> 01:33:41,800
(Remaining Skill Cards)
Restore or rewind.

2894
01:33:41,800 --> 01:33:42,280
(Item cards: Rewind Card, Free Card)
Or...

2895
01:33:42,280 --> 01:33:43,240
(Copy Card, Sing Card, Freeze Card)
Rewind Card!

2896
01:33:43,720 --> 01:33:44,920
Ning, you take the first line.

2897
01:33:44,920 --> 01:33:45,840
(Assigning tasks)
Jin, the second.

2898
01:33:45,840 --> 01:33:46,600
I'll take the third.

2899
01:33:46,600 --> 01:33:47,280
You take the fourth.

2900
01:33:47,280 --> 01:33:48,000
Then...

2901
01:33:48,000 --> 01:33:48,520
No.

2902
01:33:48,520 --> 01:33:49,520
We all take the fourth.

2903
01:33:49,520 --> 01:33:50,040
Memorize more of it.

2904
01:33:50,040 --> 01:33:50,800
(Brain storage running low)
My brain's bad.

2905
01:33:50,800 --> 01:33:52,000
Right. We'll all memorize
the fourth line.

2906
01:33:52,000 --> 01:33:52,280
Okay.

2907
01:33:52,280 --> 01:33:53,680
No. I can only remember
the third line, Ding.

2908
01:33:53,680 --> 01:33:54,840
My line's already hard.

2909
01:33:54,840 --> 01:33:55,960
Then just remember the third.

2910
01:33:55,960 --> 01:33:56,960
The three of us will do the fourth.

2911
01:33:56,960 --> 01:33:58,200
Okay.

2912
01:33:59,080 --> 01:34:00,120
My brain's bad.

2913
01:34:00,120 --> 01:34:00,800
Mine too.

2914
01:34:01,240 --> 01:34:02,200
I just felt

2915
01:34:02,200 --> 01:34:03,800
every line slipping out of my head.

2916
01:34:04,040 --> 01:34:04,560
Say it.

2917
01:34:04,780 --> 01:34:05,540
(What now?)

2918
01:34:06,280 --> 01:34:07,320
How are you acting like a big brother?

2919
01:34:07,480 --> 01:34:08,600
I am acting like one.

2920
01:34:08,600 --> 01:34:09,560
Young people have better brains.

2921
01:34:09,560 --> 01:34:10,380
(A very confident brother)

2922
01:34:10,680 --> 01:34:11,520
I have a card too.

2923
01:34:12,200 --> 01:34:13,640
(Remaining Skill Cards)
There's an Item Card.

2924
01:34:13,640 --> 01:34:15,040
(Hint Card, Item Card)
What's an Item Card?

2925
01:34:15,040 --> 01:34:16,320
(Dance Card, Massage Card x2)
A recorder?

2926
01:34:16,320 --> 01:34:16,600
Nope.

2927
01:34:17,160 --> 01:34:18,120
A Rewind Card is enough.

2928
01:34:18,120 --> 01:34:18,760
But I think

2929
01:34:18,760 --> 01:34:20,520
it may want us to copy the tune.

2930
01:34:20,520 --> 01:34:21,480
We may have to sing the tune too.

2931
01:34:21,480 --> 01:34:22,280
We have to sing it.

2932
01:34:22,480 --> 01:34:22,840
Right!

2933
01:34:23,080 --> 01:34:25,640
Did it maybe get pitch-shifted?

2934
01:34:26,240 --> 01:34:27,120
Maybe it was...

2935
01:34:27,600 --> 01:34:27,840
No.

2936
01:34:27,840 --> 01:34:29,320
Maybe it's reversed.

2937
01:34:29,320 --> 01:34:30,280
Right. It might be reversed.

2938
01:34:30,640 --> 01:34:31,000
Yeah.

2939
01:34:31,360 --> 01:34:32,680
What reversed?

2940
01:34:32,680 --> 01:34:33,800
Do none of you go online?

2941
01:34:33,800 --> 01:34:35,540
It's just an internet meme.

2942
01:34:35,540 --> 01:34:37,460
(Collective offline mode)
What meme?

2943
01:34:37,480 --> 01:34:38,920
The kind with forced rhymes.

2944
01:34:38,920 --> 01:34:40,160
Teddy crackers.

2945
01:34:40,180 --> 01:34:41,360
(Ning Waver's internet meme class)

2946
01:34:41,360 --> 01:34:42,480
It's like that, you know?

2947
01:34:42,480 --> 01:34:43,720
Like, for example...

2948
01:34:43,860 --> 01:34:46,180
(Jin Jing pretty, that's me)

2949
01:34:46,920 --> 01:34:48,120
You know? That's what it means.

2950
01:34:48,120 --> 01:34:49,120
(Got it)

2951
01:34:49,120 --> 01:34:49,600
That's how it works.

2952
01:34:49,600 --> 01:34:50,800
None of us go online.

2953
01:34:50,940 --> 01:34:53,260
(No signal here)

2954
01:34:55,680 --> 01:34:57,960
I have a card that can summon

2955
01:34:57,960 --> 01:35:00,120
an item from another timeline anytime.

2956
01:35:02,040 --> 01:35:02,640
That works.

2957
01:35:02,640 --> 01:35:03,440
A recorder.

2958
01:35:03,440 --> 01:35:04,240
Use it.

2959
01:35:04,240 --> 01:35:04,600
Let's go.

2960
01:35:04,600 --> 01:35:05,960
I'm using the Item Card!

2961
01:35:09,520 --> 01:35:11,840
What era is this thing from?

2962
01:35:11,840 --> 01:35:13,480
What is this thing, young hero?

2963
01:35:13,480 --> 01:35:14,640
(Press here)
Hold to record.

2964
01:35:14,640 --> 01:35:16,720
Press once after recording to play it.

2965
01:35:16,720 --> 01:35:17,800
We still need the Rewind aCrd.

2966
01:35:17,800 --> 01:35:18,560
Rewind Card.

2967
01:35:18,880 --> 01:35:19,960
Rewind Card!

2968
01:35:21,260 --> 01:35:24,660
(Rewind Card: Makes the NPC in the game
immediately repeat the last line once)

2969
01:35:41,640 --> 01:35:42,960
I remember it right.

2970
01:36:02,200 --> 01:36:03,760
I remember it right.

2971
01:36:06,920 --> 01:36:07,760
I got it this time.

2972
01:36:07,760 --> 01:36:08,880
I even remember the tune.

2973
01:36:09,280 --> 01:36:09,880
Okay, play it again.

2974
01:36:13,560 --> 01:36:14,400
Songsong Biscuit.

2975
01:36:14,400 --> 01:36:15,240
You still got it wrong.

2976
01:36:15,240 --> 01:36:16,080
Songsong Biscuit.

2977
01:36:16,080 --> 01:36:17,040
Let's go!

2978
01:36:21,440 --> 01:36:22,120
Come on.

2979
01:36:23,260 --> 01:36:24,500
Songsong Biscuit!

2980
01:36:24,540 --> 01:36:25,160
I...

2981
01:36:36,110 --> 01:36:38,240
I soar into the sky.

2982
01:36:38,240 --> 01:36:39,350
To greet..

2983
01:36:40,980 --> 01:36:45,240
My empty heart.

2984
01:36:56,880 --> 01:36:58,160
My back just tingled.

2985
01:37:03,280 --> 01:37:04,680
Is something gonna show up?

2986
01:37:16,280 --> 01:37:17,800
What's that smoke up ahead?

2987
01:37:18,760 --> 01:37:19,880
Stop messing around.

2988
01:37:19,880 --> 01:37:21,360
Stop it, man.

2989
01:37:39,040 --> 01:37:39,840
A boat's coming!

2990
01:37:40,600 --> 01:37:41,640
There really is.

2991
01:37:41,640 --> 01:37:42,480
Is that a boat?

2992
01:37:42,800 --> 01:37:43,320
Yes.

2993
01:37:46,480 --> 01:37:47,440
We're done, man.

2994
01:37:49,240 --> 01:37:51,400
No, someone's rowing it.

2995
01:37:53,960 --> 01:37:55,120
On that boat...

2996
01:37:55,120 --> 01:37:58,380
(What exactly is coming to greet them?)

2997
01:38:08,020 --> 01:38:09,380
(Night Visit to the Ghost Market:
Ghost Soldiers Lead the Souls)

2998
01:38:09,380 --> 01:38:09,920
(Next Episode Preview)

2999
01:38:09,920 --> 01:38:10,560
Look behind you!

3000
01:38:10,560 --> 01:38:11,200
Behind you guys.

3001
01:38:12,240 --> 01:38:13,520
Stop it, man.

3002
01:38:13,520 --> 01:38:15,280
We've finally reached the Ghost Market.

3003
01:38:15,280 --> 01:38:15,840
What is that?

3004
01:38:15,960 --> 01:38:17,160
This place is way too creepy.

3005
01:38:17,160 --> 01:38:18,000
I'm kinda scared.

3006
01:38:18,120 --> 01:38:18,680
Don't!

3007
01:38:20,560 --> 01:38:21,440
Man.

3008
01:38:21,440 --> 01:38:24,290
The Ghost Market is open!

3009
01:38:24,520 --> 01:38:25,970
Come take a look!

3010
01:38:26,000 --> 01:38:27,190
Come check it out!

3011
01:38:27,480 --> 01:38:28,780
That's the fortune-telling stall.

3012
01:38:28,840 --> 01:38:29,640
He's our best bet.

3013
01:38:29,640 --> 01:38:30,980
(Mystery of the Black Tower:
The Dead Return)

3014
01:38:31,200 --> 01:38:33,640
Why didn't Ning Waver die?

3015
01:38:33,640 --> 01:38:36,920
Have you forgotten the legend
of the Ghost Soldiers reviving the dead?

3016
01:38:36,920 --> 01:38:38,360
There was a mysterious person.

3017
01:38:38,360 --> 01:38:40,680
We circled him a full 360 degrees.

3018
01:38:40,680 --> 01:38:41,720
But we only saw his back.

3019
01:38:41,720 --> 01:38:42,480
He has no face.

3020
01:38:42,480 --> 01:38:43,280
Thousand-Faced Eagle King.

3021
01:38:43,280 --> 01:38:45,200
He lives at the top of this Black Tower.

3022
01:38:46,320 --> 01:38:47,200
Who's crying?

3023
01:38:47,520 --> 01:38:49,040
He used the Ghost Soldiers
as an excuse to hurt children.

3024
01:38:49,360 --> 01:38:50,240
Hurt children?

3025
01:38:50,480 --> 01:38:52,240
He used both of them to frame someone.

3026
01:38:52,240 --> 01:38:53,720
He's close with that doctor.

3027
01:38:53,720 --> 01:38:54,560
It was Shi Damen.

3028
01:38:54,560 --> 01:38:57,120
Someone used
the Heart-Sucking Mark on you.

3029
01:38:57,120 --> 01:38:57,920
Doctor Gui.

3030
01:38:58,160 --> 01:39:00,320
His pulse will tell us everything.

3031
01:39:00,320 --> 01:39:01,680
Wait. Why can't I feel your pulse?

3032
01:39:03,400 --> 01:39:04,760
He's already dead!

3033
01:39:04,760 --> 01:39:05,560
What?

3034
01:39:06,140 --> 01:39:07,500
(Following the Clues: Everyone
Has Their Own Agenda)

3035
01:39:07,600 --> 01:39:08,960
Hold on.

3036
01:39:09,280 --> 01:39:10,920
Isn't this that body?

3037
01:39:11,320 --> 01:39:12,000
What are you doing?

3038
01:39:13,160 --> 01:39:14,400
We can use the body's position

3039
01:39:14,400 --> 01:39:15,440
to work backward.

3040
01:39:15,440 --> 01:39:16,960
Whoever has
the Qide Sword is the killer.

3041
01:39:16,960 --> 01:39:19,120
It was Ning Waver fighting Lord Tui.

3042
01:39:19,120 --> 01:39:21,680
Ning Waver is the one
who knew that secret manual.

3043
01:39:21,680 --> 01:39:24,120
I believe he wouldn't do that.

3044
01:39:24,120 --> 01:39:25,960
So I'm the petty villain.

3045
01:39:26,400 --> 01:39:29,160
A scheming little killer.

3046
01:39:29,160 --> 01:39:29,960
I'm suspicious.

3047
01:39:29,960 --> 01:39:30,520
It's you.

3048
01:39:30,520 --> 01:39:31,880
Why are you so quick to defend yourself?

3049
01:39:31,880 --> 01:39:32,320
It's not me.

3050
01:39:32,840 --> 01:39:35,320
The killer's guilt is plain to see.

3051
01:39:35,520 --> 01:39:36,680
He's highly suspicious.

3052
01:39:36,680 --> 01:39:38,000
Because he found this letter.

3053
01:39:38,000 --> 01:39:39,360
That's disgraceful.

3054
01:39:39,840 --> 01:39:40,720
A total frame-up.

3055
01:39:41,120 --> 01:39:41,920
He's dead for sure.

